post_text:
As a foreign student, I couldn't be happier to have come to Leeds to get my degree. Moving countries is tough AF, you leave a lot behind, but coming here was one of the best things that's happened to me. I thought that I would have trouble adapting here and fitting in, but it's been the complete opposite. I feel like I can be myself here without being judged and I have an amazing group of friends that make me feel at home.

Thank you for being so amazing,

Love,
A v drunk international student xxx
name: LeedsFess

post_text: Such a stigma for non drinkers here - I feel so pressured to drink. Like the other night I was racking up slugs of k in the Klute toilets and people were look at me like I’m some kind of ‘loser’ or ‘freak’.

How do you find people to live with in second year? Everyone I've approached is already in with another group of friends so I'm scared I'm going to be on my own. I really can't afford a studio and also I'm worried that if I live on my own I'll just never go out or interact with other people so will miss out on a bunch of stuff or just have a really shit second year and lose what little social life I have already
name: Newfess
